WEBVTT

00:00.320 --> 00:03.832
Change into passive. He's playing football. She was playing football.

00:03.936 --> 00:07.464
They will play football. He has played football. We had played football.

00:07.552 --> 00:11.224
I can play football. I want to change all these sentences into passive.

00:11.272 --> 00:14.600
It's not at all rocket science. Just start with the object football,

00:14.720 --> 00:19.384
football, football, football, football, football. And then put the past participle

00:19.432 --> 00:23.400
of the verb at the end. The past of play is played,

00:23.520 --> 00:27.720
played, played, played, played, played. And then look before the verb.

00:27.800 --> 00:30.784
You'll find these words is, was, will,

00:30.872 --> 00:34.688
has, had, can and so on. Just write them down here and

00:34.744 --> 00:38.240
then write be or been or being. Here we

00:38.280 --> 00:41.552
have playing with ing, so being with ing.

00:41.616 --> 00:45.152
And here too, playing, being here play so be

00:45.256 --> 00:49.184
here played so been played here, so been play here

00:49.272 --> 00:52.656
so be. These are the answers. Now you answer

00:52.688 --> 00:56.848
this one. We may play football. Can you change it into passive?

00:56.944 --> 00:57.720
Let me see in the comments.
